01:28:52.270 --> 01:28:53.570
Thank you.

01:28:53.570 --> 01:28:55.970
Any questions, feel
free to get up and ask.

01:29:00.200 --> 01:29:01.500
&gt;&gt; This question [inaudible].

01:29:01.500 --> 01:29:10.540
It would seem to me that
the foundation has been laid

01:29:10.540 --> 01:29:17.930
for international children's
literature.

01:29:17.930 --> 01:29:19.230
I'm overwhelmed.

01:29:19.230 --> 01:29:36.120 position:56%
I'm so very, very moved by what I've
seen and learned, and yet I can feel

01:29:36.120 --> 01:29:38.190
that it's this universal
[inaudible],

01:29:38.190 --> 01:29:40.480 position:56%
it's all of the children everywhere.

01:29:40.480 --> 01:29:41.780
&gt;&gt; Homan Yamini Sharif: Exactly.

01:29:41.780 --> 01:29:44.530
Well, I think there are two
probably periods in our life

01:29:44.530 --> 01:29:48.410 position:56%
that this [inaudible] really becomes
meaningful as a child and then

01:29:48.410 --> 01:29:51.900
at the end of life, that
wholeness comes back to us.

01:29:51.900 --> 01:29:55.860
So it is pretty much the same
concept and same stories here

01:29:55.860 --> 01:29:59.890
as probably has been in one way
or another has been repeated

01:29:59.890 --> 01:30:04.060 position:56%
in other nations and they came of
people from different period of time

01:30:04.060 --> 01:30:06.060
when children were not
really paid attention to

01:30:06.060 --> 01:30:11.780
and they started writing and
bringing a new world to children.

